{
  "texts": [
    "From Fig. 13, we observe that M8F8 does not result in any notable increase in perplexity.",
    "The M8F4 quantization exhibits a slight increase in perplexity, though still indicating stable model performance.",
    "In contrast, the perplexity increase is noticeable for the M4F8.",
    "This is attributed to the greater dynamic range observed in the weights in MHA when compared to FF weights during quantization.",
    "Overall, we observe that M8F4 outperforms M4F8 in terms of both model stability and energy efficiency."
  ]
}